--[[
    ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ║           ScriptCapture GUI — LocalScript Detector          ║
    ║  Detects executed LocalScripts, captures their code/info,   ║
    ║  displays it in a draggable GUI with a Copy button.         ║
    ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

    HOW TO USE:
      1. Paste this script into a LocalScript inside StarterPlayerScripts
         (or execute it via an executor).
      2. Any LocalScript that runs under LocalPlayer will be detected.
      3. Click a captured script entry to view its details.
      4. Use the [Copy] button to copy the full captured report.

    NOTE ON .Source:
      • In Studio (Play Solo), .Source is readable with the right permissions.
      • In a live game, Roblox restricts .Source for security reasons.
        If you're using an executor that grants decompilation/source access,
        the script will capture full source automatically.
      • Without .Source access, the script captures all available metadata,
        hierarchy, properties, and a reconstructed report.
--]]

